# CLAUDE.md.example -- The Prover (Template)

This file documents the expected structure of the `CLAUDE.md` that belongs in this directory.
The actual `CLAUDE.md` is excluded from version control (see `../NOTICE.md`).

## Purpose

The Prover is the fourth and final agent in the pipeline. It certifies the mathematical
truth of the system by proving in Coq that the implementation is isomorphic to the
specification. If the Prover certifies a unit, the network trusts that code. If it finds
a bug, the pipeline halts.

## Expected CLAUDE.md Sections

1. Identity and Context (final gate in pipeline)
2. Dual-Directory Model (agent infra in lab/, proofs in validium/proofs/ or zkl2/proofs/)
3. Verification Unit Structure (0-input-spec/, 0-input-impl/, 1-proofs/, 2-reports/)
4. Operational Principles (isomorphism, mathematical rigor, skeptic's mindset)
5. Multi-Language Modeling (TypeScript, Go, Rust, Solidity, Circom -> Coq)
6. Two Modes of Operation (Mode A: Verification, Mode B: Audit)
7. Standard Library (Common.v: TLA+ and implementation type mappings)
8. Proof File Conventions (Spec.v, Impl.v, Refinement.v)
9. Tooling (Coq runner, verification unit generator)
10. Git Workflow and Documentation Standards

## Expected Skills (.claude/commands/)

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `/verify` | Construct Coq proofs for a new verification unit |
| `/audit` | Audit existing proofs for completeness and faithfulness |
| `/status` | Verification status check |
